SIMPLE: solidarity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Solidarity
<hw>Sol`i*dar"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>solidarit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, fr. <ets>solide</ets>. See
<er>Solid</er>.]</ety> <def>An entire union or consolidation of
interests and responsibilities; fellowship; community.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Solidarity</qex> [a word which we owe to the French
Communists], signifies a fellowship in gain and loss, in honor and
dishonor, in victory and defeat, a being, so to speak, all in the same
boat.</q> <rj><qau>Trench.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>solidarity</qex> . . . of Breton and Welsh poetry.</q>
<rj><qau>M. Arnold.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solidary</ent>⟦br⟧
